# UI Components

Source: `Plans/17-ui-components.md`. Read it before any UI work.

## Product UI principles

- Minimalist UI, maximalist backend — minimum typing, rest inferred/defaulted
- **Three-input rule:** ≤3 inputs above the fold; progressive disclosure for the rest
- Premium jewellery aesthetic — not Material/Ant enterprise look

## Reuse decision tree (mandatory)

```
1. packages/ui/COMPONENTS.md → exists? Import from @sonari/ui
2. IndiaCN catalog → exists? Copy into packages/ui/india/, adapt tokens
3. shadcn catalog → exists? pnpm dlx shadcn add <name> into packages/ui
4. Truly reusable? Build in packages/ui, update COMPONENTS.md
   One-off only? apps/*/components/ with // TODO: promote if reused
```

## Hard rules

- Apps import **only** from `@sonari/ui` — never `@radix-ui/*`, `lucide-react`, `cmdk` directly
- Shared components live in `packages/ui` (primitives / india / compound / layouts)
- India fields use india components: `RupeeInput`, `GstinInput`, `HuidInput`, `WeightInput`, `PurityInput`, etc.
- Design tokens only — no one-off hex colors; use CSS variables in `tokens.css`
- Every screen: loading, empty, error states · mobile 375px · keyboard navigable

## Stack

Vite SPA + React Router v6 data routers · Tailwind · shadcn/ui + IndiaCN · Radix · Lucide via `@sonari/ui` · Zustand + TanStack Query · RHF + Zod
